"reviewcomment":"&#34;Thank you bad weather/rain! Because of you, I&#39;ve discovered this great place!&#34;<br><br>Thanks to bad weather, we decided to skip our walk along the shops and ducked into this cafe. Also, we were rather captivated by the delicious bakery-like smell enamating from its doors.<br><br>Expect to wait about 15 mins for a seat if you are in a group of 3 or more. Lucky for us, we were good with the window seat, which allows us to enjoy the rain-soaked streets of Paris and passerbys hurrying along.<br><br>We knew that the portions in Paris were huge, hence, we ordered just one cup of Hot Chocolate. Chocolate lovers will definitely love this drink - its texture was creamy, smooth and fragrant. Two sips would send you into aphrodisiac heaven! A very good drink to share on a rainy Thursday afternoon in Paris.<br><br>Service was excellent (staff really know the menu well and gave good recommendations) and the ambience was top-notch (everything you would expect from a cafe in Paris).<br><br>We didn&#39;t manage to try the dessert at this outlet but had a chocolate éclair at an outlet nearer our hotel.<br><br>Heard the gelatos were famous and will be sure to get some the next time around.",
