"reviewcomment":"After hearing only good things about Colorova I decided to take my family here when they came to visit. It was such a pleasant experience that I plan on bringing all future visitors here for breakfast! <br><br>The decor is really quirky and unlike any other place in Paris. It is so original to see something different in Paris and to see bright and colourful art covering the walls. <br><br>What I was most surprised at was how reasonably priced the breakfast menu here was. I would even be tempted to say it is one of the most reasonable breakfasts I&#39;ve come across. For 12 euro you&#39;ll receive a selection jams and chocolate spread with bread, a fruit compote with fromage frais, French toast, a hot drink and a glass of freshly squeezed orange juice. Everything which we tried was delicious and I was thankful for a refreshingly different breakfast menu which forced me to try things which I might not ordinarily have chosen. <br><br>The service was wonderful and the experience was ever so happy.<br><br>The patisseries in the cabinet looked divine, whilst we didn&#39;t get the chance to try them I&#39;m sure they would taste as good as they look. Another thing which always pleases me is being able to see a chef at work and here you&#39;re able to see through to the kitchen where the pastry chef was carefully putting together her beautiful creations.",
