"categorystrlist":"French,     Cafes,     Coffee & Tea",
"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/assets/2/www/img/76df14aad260/default_avatars/business_large_square.png",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Thanks yelp for this find!  There are lots of cute restaurants and cafes in the St. Germaine area and looked to yelp to help us find a place for lunch and looked around for it.  We accidentally went into Le Bistro d&#39;Henri as the Yelp app map was a bit wonky.. they rubbed us a bit the wrong way as we stepped out, they locked the door behind us... and it wasn&#39;t even that late into lunch time.  <br><br>We were about to go to this other restaurant and this place caught our eye and only later realised we ended up at the place we originally wanted to go to in the first place. It&#39;s a small cozy place where they have the menus listed on a black chalk board.  Luckily my friends knew a little bit of French but with things like Google Translate, we easily picked out courses.  <br><br>I had the terrine of courgette to start.  It was egg with courgette and a side of cold tomato sauce.  It tasted fresh and delicious.  Needed a tad bit of salt but I prefer it this way as opposed to things being too salty.  For my main I had the onglet of veal and this was amazing.  At first glance, the sauce looked a bit too creamy but it was perfect in the end.  It came with a side of creamy potatoes which topped it off really well.  The place isn&#39;t too great for vegetarians as the only main option was to pull together a plate of veggies (tomato, green beans, cabbage).  <br><br>One thing I love about France is ordering the table wine.  It was only about 9 euros for a bottle and it was great.  Quite a young wine but easy drinking.  Alternatively, they had a good selection of wine if you fancy something else.  <br><br>Service was great and would definitely come back for some more.",
