"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"This little wine shop is on kind of an obscure off-street and we wouldn&#39;t have gone in if it weren&#39;t for the fact that were were heading home the next day and wanted to bring back some bottles. (For the record, words cannot describe how good and CHEAP wine is in France.) <br><br>When we walked in we were immediately welcomed and offered a taste. They were sampling four different kinds that day and when we had trouble picking one, the person working there just said, &#34;how about all four?&#34; So all together, we probably had a whole glass of free wine while the worker educated us about where it was from and how it was made. A little after that we noticed one of the people working spoke English with an American accent. We got to talking with him and discovered he&#39;s from the US and went to college in our home region of the northwest. We bought a bottle, and went on our way. <br><br>I was compelled to write this review because I was very impressed with the service, the samples, and the fact that an American works there. Don&#39;t get me wrong, all the French people we met were lovely, but sometimes it can feel a little isolating surrounded by people who live so far from you; it&#39;s comforting to talk with someone who can relate. Also, the same owners own a couple restaurants nearby, Cosi, Semilla, and Fish. We didn&#39;t get a chance to go to any of them but I have heard good things.",
