"rating":"5.0",
"reviewcomment":"Everywhere you go in Paris, you will find a wine store or wine bar on any street corner. I love my wine and it&#39;s oh so convenient but damn it I love my beer. I have found my beer haven at last. <br>A couple of minutes from Abbesses station, this store is open from noon until late. Everyday! There is nothing wrong with having a beer at noon on a day off right? Plus, with the time change, it&#39;s probably beer o&#39;clock anyways.<br>Choose from over a thousand bottles to take with you to a pique-nique or just to enjoy at home. Or choose a bottle and have it chilled in a matter of minutes and enjoy at the store. Sit at the communal table and chat with the owner and the locals. <br>My French is minimal. Very. But this is the type of place where you don&#39;t get the attitude and you can just relax and enjoy some really good beer. <br>Don&#39;t forget to take a moment to take in the interior design. The details and thought put into the shop is oh so cool.<br><br>Just a tip: ( I found out the hard way ) If you&#39;re getting off at Abbesses do take the elevator instead of the stairs. You&#39;ll thank me later.<br><br>8/100",
