"reviewcomment":"First of all, this is the fanciest Starbucks I have ever visited. <br><br>We were on our way to Galeries Lafayette when we stumbled upon this location. We were just going to grab-and-go but after seeing the interior decor of this place, we had to stay and enjoy it a little bit. <br><br>It is so pretty inside; it felt like we were having afternoon tea at the palace. It is actually quite big, but it was incredibly busy and loud. People were waiting in different areas, trying to spot where others were about to get up and leave (similar to eating at a busy food court). <br><br>This was our first time visiting Starbucks in Europe. The pastries are a little different from Toronto, but we did not try them (considering there are so many better patisseries in Paris!). With regards to the costs, we notice the pricing system was quite similar to others stores in Paris that we have in Canada as well. Basically the numbers were quite the same but in euros; i.e. a tall coffee costs $2 with change in Toronto, while it costs 2€ in Paris.",
