"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/eVnpHudl2rhxJpXCemLlRw/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"This is something else. My wife and I went there to celebrate her 65th. We went for three days and I told her that we would be going to the station cafe at the Garde de Lyons for her birthday meal. Did she get a surprise, so did I as the bill came to £250, but you can do things for a little over half that.<br><br> We had a four course meal, and the nice thing was, all the better wines on the menu were also available in half bottles. So we had half a bottle of a top marque champagne with our first course and half a bottle of a fantastic Burgundy, the best I have ever supped.<br><br> The food just can&#39;t be described and all I can say is that it was everything they say about French gourmet cooking!<br><br> The service was as one would expect, impeccable, and the waiters were as aoof as one would expect with English speaking customers. However when I have them a special card I have written in French, the gist being &#34;Alas, I speak three languages, English, Afrikaans and Zulu, but am too old to now learn a fourth one. French is not used in South Africa and, alas, Zulu is not very useful in France&#34;. This usually creates a little smile and we got on much better after that.<br><br> I might go back, but at the price, and looking at my pension, it would have to be a very special occasion.<br><br>UPDATE: Somebody, either at Qype or Yelp changed the name and address. The restaurant is called &#34;Le Trein Bleu&#34; and it is inside the Gare de Lyon.",
