"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Sits right in front of the Jardin du Luxembourg with outdoor seating (I think!). <br><br>Tried the famous Opera cake here and it was ridiculous. The idea doesn&#39;t seem like it&#39;d be novel, just a chocolate cake made with tons of tiny layers on layers. But the cake is just stunning from the first bite to the last. Those layers really do make all the difference in the whole experience of devouring it (which happened pretty fast). I wish I had tried other things here because, judging by the taste of this cake, I&#39;m sure they would have been delicious. It is a little pricey though with the one slice at 5 euros. It was a fairly thin slice too but very rich and smooth. <br><br>This place also actually has a pretty interesting history too. I ended up including it in a school assignment and it turns out that the founder of this patisserie was part of the court at Versailles...! It&#39;s crazy to think since it&#39;s now a chain and you can walk by one of these shops all over Paris without even knowing about the wealth of history behind it. Just another thing to love about Europe and Paris -- how much history is weaved into the random streets you&#39;ll walk on the daily.",
