"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Pretty fantastic stuff Chef Cherrier makes. I was intrigued. I Googled the place before coming to Paris, &amp; saw a ton of pics of Chef Cherrier. I kind of wanted to see him there - the master in action - but fat chance, he wasn&#39;t there. I still feel bad for what I did, but um, I did something bad when I went in there: I asked for directions to the Moulin Rouge (which, btw, was a big disappointment).<br><br>They did give us directions, &amp; the guy that helped us had a somewhat annoyed look on his face. I would&#39;ve been annoyed, too, but my maps app stopped working &amp; I wanted to justify the trip to the boulangerie to my cousin. lol. But oui, The Moulin Rouge was the side trip - not the boulangerie ;) I pulled this off smoothly by saying something like &#34;Oh look, Gontran Cherrier. We might as well go in &amp; ask for directions.&#34; As if I just happened to wander over to the area.<br><br>Inside, I asked the girl, &#34;Parlez-vous Anglais?&#34; She said no. Oh noes. In my broken French I asked her what was &#34;bon&#34; (I may have asked tres bon, or something, &amp; pointed at the desserts) &amp; she said her favorite was the citron thingy. I got that, plus this thing with like cream cheese, in the form of a mousse, with dots of what looked like tiny shavings of lime (after some Googling, I now know that was the &#34;Tarte au fromage blanc&#34;, which I think translates to white cheese tart, &amp; it cost €4,30).<br><br>The citron 1 that was the favorite of the pretty French girl from Gontran Cherrier turned out to be a bit too sour for me, but the 1 with the moussey cheese or cheesy mousse with lime shavings - the Tarte au fromage blanc - was ah-may-zinnng :]]",
