"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/D7isI1c_OX0h6zkjIBxs6Q/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I live a 15 minute bike ride from this boulangerie and I make the trip here at least once a week. I do not know why there is so much hype around these boutique eclair shops in the Marais, nothing can compete with the chocolate, pistachio or coffee eclairs I have had here. I cant even begin to write about the apricot torte or the rhubarb cake, both of which are the perfect balance of tart and sweet, crumbly crust and melting filling. <br><br> The rustic fig bread or walnut and fruit bread are both incredible; often, breads with dried fruits skimp on the proportion but here, every bite is filled with flavor and generous chunks of fruit. The goat cheese walnut quiche or the three vegetable (eggplant, tomato, zucchini) quiche both have a fantastic balance of flavor and texture. Combined with a little something sweet, you have the perfect picnic in the Parc right next door. <br><br>A friend of mine lives close to this shop and had some of the chocolate eclairs specially made for a party and all three of the giant eclairs disappeared withing two minutes of them being brought out. The dark chocolate flowed out of the perfect dough and everybody was licking their fingers after devouring their slice of the eclair-cake. Whenever anybody visits me in Paris now,  I insist that this bakery is a *must* on their tourist itinerary. While visiting the US for Christmas, I keep thinking that the first thing I plan on doing as soon as I get back to Paris is to buy some sweet treat and take a stroll in the Parc; nothing could be a more perfect homecoming.",
