"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I had lunch at this bar/restaurant about 4 years ago on the recommendation of a Time Out guide and liked it so much that I went back this weekend to see if it had changed at all. It&#39;s supposed to be one of the &#39;hippest&#39; places in Paris apparently, although I really only went back for the salad, as it was probably one of the most beautiful things I have ever seen. Covered in all kinds of berries and colourful fruits, it was a delicous monster of a salad, completely not what I was expecting when I ordered it. <br>Unfortunately, on this occasion, it was far too cold for salad, so I went for soup instead. It was very tasty - a chestnutty concoction - but well overpriced. The service on this occasion was rather sharp too (I know, I know - it was Paris - but I have to say that the service was better last time, so maybe in their &#39;hip-ness&#39; they&#39;ve become a little complacent?<br>All in all, I think their reputation of being &#39;trendy&#39; pretty much outweighs the quality of the place these days. I came away rather disappointed, whereas last time I was blown away.",
