"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"C&#39;est Magnifique<br><br>While stumbling through the streets of Paris I came across many a chocolate stores but none quite like this..... The walls were packed with colourful displays of a mix of both chocolates and candies. A giant fountain of chocolate sprang to life as we entered the shop. After filling our bags with any and every kind of truffle we could find we found ourselves eyeing the pot of hot chocolate by the cash register. Although we had to wait about 5 minutes or so for it to heat up it was well worth the wait. It ended up possibly being the best hot chocolate I have ever tasted in my LIFE....imagine what the chocolate river in Charlie and The Chocolate Factory would taste like and multiply it by about 100..... Sweet but not too sweet, thick but not too thick, hot but not too hot! After arriving back at the hotel we were pleasantly surprised by the same kind of deliciousness in our truffles....so much so that we ate them all in one sitting and will most likely have to pay another visit to the shop before we leave on Friday! I highly recommend that if you find yourself in the area you should stop by and enjoy all that deNeuville has to offer, particularly the hot chocolate!",
