"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"They carry everything from groceries, cosmetics, to everyday household items, clothing and the list goes on and on. I would agree that Monoprix is similar to a Target in the States. <br><br>We did buy some clothes for our god daughter here as a gift to bring back. While in Target, you&#39;d probably see in the toddler section a bright pink shirt with a cutesy phrase written in very large glittered font splashed in front. I&#39;ve noticed in this country there are smarter and muted sartorial options for kids while still managing to look adorable without the hefty price. We picked up the following for her: a navy/white striped tank, a grey cardigan sweater with elbow patches (it was from the boy&#39;s section but looked very stylish on her!) and a chambray dress. They were all things we see for probably 4x the cost in toddler boutique stores but were reasonably priced here.<br><br>For us we picked up some bottles of water and snacks to take home to our flat. <br><br>We&#39;ll be heading back to Paris again next month and I imagine we&#39;ll probably make a couple trips to Monoprix.",
