"reviewcomment":"Our apartment was directly across the street from Bellota-Bellota. It is a small shop with the delectable Iberian ham hanging in the windows. Although Iberian ham is from Spain it can be found all over Paris. <br><br>You may be asking yourself why I want to go to Paris and try ham? It is an experience that should not miss. The ham does not taste like the ham we are used to in America. The flavors are so much better and its cut paper thin and just melts away in your mouth. Pair it with a local red wine and you are good to go.<br><br>It can get pricey especially for the black footed ham but you should try it. You can really taste the grasses and the acorns in the meat which gives off a pleasant flavor and aroma. <br><br>Melt in your mouth goodness!",
