"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"This is a great little bakery that&#39;s conveniently located right outside of the Cambronne exit of the Paris Metro.<br><br>We had just arrived in Paris and I was totally spent after a long day of traveling, but the minute I exited the Metro and caught a whiff of Boulangerie Weiland I instantly started floating across the street like Tucan Sam following his nose to a bowl of Fruit Loops.<br><br>Upon entering it&#39;s not a very big bakery at all, but it was packed with all sorts of sweet and savory items. I got a tartine with chorizo which is kind of like a French bread pizza and it was just amazing. I also got a croissant which was perfectly flaky, buttery and soft. The next morning I got a couple pan au chocolates and was hooked like a crack junkie for the rest of our stay...seriously, I think I ate over a dozen of them over the span of three days. We tried some other things as well and everything blew the socks off of the crappy bakeries here in the United States.<br><br>Also, the service here was fantastic and I was always greeted with a warm smile by everyone. They didn&#39;t speak English by the way, but I am extremely proficient in smiling and pointing so it wasn&#39;t much of an issue for me.<br><br>All in all I should thank the Food Gods for having this place so close to our hotel in Paris and I really wish that I had one of their delicious pan au chocolates right now....yum!",
