"reviewcomment":"This was an awesome find! We had stopped here for coffee on the way back to our apartment near the Bastille. We came back here another day for lunch after seeing the yummy dishes that other customers were having.<br>Food: Wonderful! My husband had a burger served with fries and it was delicious. So were the frogs legs that I had, served on a bed of rice with salad. It had a great creamy sauce that I completely devoured.<br>Ambiance: the inside is small like most Parisian brasseries and was warm and cozy. Looked slightly more upscale than others in the area. We sat outside enjoying the street scene and the unseasonably warm weather.<br>Service: The service was great. The waitstaff spoke english and was friendly and helpful. There was a slight mishap with my frogs legs. The dish toppled off the small table and was saved but some of the contents had spilled (fortunately I was not at the table at that time) onto the table and my chair. Staff leaped into action cleaning up the mess and was very apologetic. The host offered us some Champagne on the house which was a really nice gesture!<br>I highly reccomend  this restaurant and look forward to our next visit!",
