"reviewcomment":"This is my bagel place. Not because the bagels are amazing. But because they are good, the choices are well balanced, and the staff is super nice. Aaaand....I work 3 minutes away walking. <br><br>The prices are a little steep for the desserts - but they are really yummy. I would say that they need to step up their bagel quality (they are a little bit small/thin and they could be less dense - plus they should start serving everything bagels) and they could put a little more meat in the sandwich (but the pastrami is pretty good - but imagine if it was hot!!). If they make even some of these changes, they will be good to go. They serve Root Beer and Dr. Pepper (which is awesome) but they are super expensive (2.90 euros for a can so like 4 bucks!). <br><br>Pour les françaises, ce n&#39;est pas NYC (et ce n&#39;est surtout pas Bergen Bagels de Brooklyn) mais bon, a Paris, on ne trouve pas beaucoup mieux... (Mais si tu sais ou, dis-moi!!)",
