"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I arrived the day there was a big protest in the city at the end of March and our hotel happened to be right by it. I won&#39;t say what it was about but most who watched the news will probably know of it. I wanted to get out of that area tout de suite. What bettter way to spend a Sunday afternoon than strolling the streets of The Marais, which also happens to be the gay quarter?<br> My colleague and I spent browsing the shops and came across this bustling store. I peer in and notice this small store jam packed (pun intended) with jars upon jars of jams and jellies. <br>The jars were organized by ingredient, season, purpose, and colour. The best part? That you can sample them! I saw that they had my favourite morello cherry (cerise griotte) jam. <br>We had been walking for a good hour so sampling all the sweet preserves gave us a boost for the rest of our day. <br>As soon as I came home, I cut up some French bread, sliced a few pieces of brie and smothered them with the cherry jam. I was in heaven.<br>It was quite busy in the store but the sales reps were very helpful and politely reminded us to not double dip. There were a few patrons in there that looked suspicious...<br><br>6/100",
