"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"This probably the only place I have ever encountered the mythical poor service in Paris. It was unfortunately delivered by a young teenager who was apparently annoyed by my basic french and gave some attitude. This was quickly resolved when I asked him if he spoke English, Spanish or German, to which he answered no on all counts.<br>So I reminded him in Spanish that I spoke 3 languages, which was 2 more than his single tongue and so he needed to chill out, since I was the paying customer. After going through several shades of red, rage I pressume, he quickly realized that in the western world, the paying customer should be treated with respect.... The same respect, I may add that I had been treating him with, until he decided to be snot nose.<br>I must give him credit for his quick turnaround since from that moment on, he became the helpful, polite young man, that his parents no doubt raised him to be.<br>The manager also smoothed things over, by promptly getting involved and speaking to us in pretty good Spanish and also gave us a card good for 1 hour of Wi FI access so cheers for making it right.<br>Coffee, baguettes, sandwiches and OJ and we were ready to tackle the frigid Parisian morning.",
