"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Move over macarons, I&#39;ve found my new favorite Parisian pastries. Eclair&#39;s&#39; have always been my favorite, but L&#39;Atelier puts an elegant spin on the classic.<br><br>During my visit, I went wild and ordered 10 mini eclairs. 5 savory 5 sweet.<br><br>Yes, they make savory eclairs. I ordered the foie gras eclair, jambon comte, catalante and baltique. The eclairs are basically split in half and stuffed with a savory delicacy of your choice. The exterier bread had a soft sweetness to it which complimented the saltiness of the interior contents. Everything was amazing, but the foie gras and salmon were definately my favorites. Oh, and the jambon. Oh, dangit. nevermind. they were all equally amazing and delicious.<br><br>For the sweets, I ordered a wide variety of basically most of the display case. Nutella, Cafe, Caramel, Chocolate, green tea..YUM!<br><br>Each eclair is made with love, the presentation was beautiful, and the taste was amazing. YUMMMMMMMY!",
